264 1252 486 (         24.1.1, 24.1.3 p24-2,4:) 486 SB
264 1302 749 (   Should operator->* be added for iterators?) 749 SB
264 1352 1081 (      Section 14.3.3 [temp.opref] specifically allows operator-> to) 1081 SB
264 1402 1168 (      appear in a template where its return type cannot be dereferenced) 1168 SB
264 1452 1085 (      if it is not used.  No such guarantee is made for operator->*.) 1085 SB
264 1502 1106 (      If operator->* is desired, the same guarantee should be made.) 1106 SB
264 1602 1173 (      A proposal to change the core language to have operator->* work) 1173 SB
264 1652 1149 (      in a similar fashion to operator-> was rejected at the Santa Cruz) 1149 SB
264 1702 213 (      meeting.) 213 SB
264 1802 1073 (      Including operator->* in an iterator \(or auto_ptr\) requires a) 1073 SB
264 1852 984 (      series of member templates, helper classes, and partial) 984 SB
264 1902 309 (      specialization.) 309 SB
264 2002 1021 (   Does operator-> work correctly for input iterators? \(*a can) 1021 SB
264 2052 329 (   return an rvalue\).) 329 SB
1689 352 203 ( Resolution:) 203 SB
1689 402 462 ( Requestor:      Library WG) 462 SB
1689 452 690 ( Owner:          David Dodgson \(Iterators\)) 690 SB
1689 502 575 ( Emails:         lib-4301,4559-4560) 575 SB
