1689 852 899 ( Title:          Const Attribute in Iterator Requirements) 899 SB
1689 902 310 ( Section:        24.1) 310 SB
1689 952 324 ( Status:         active) 324 SB
1689 1002 219 ( Description:) 219 SB
1689 1052 185 (         24.1:) 185 SB
1689 1102 978 (  The tables in Clause 24 of Iterator Requirements include) 978 SB
1689 1152 1036 (  mutative operations such as ++ and =, but make no mention) 1036 SB
1689 1202 1068 (  of constness.  We should distinguish which operations require) 1068 SB
1689 1252 1038 (  a non-const operand and which can be performed on a const) 1038 SB
1689 1302 846 (  operand.  \(e.g. is *a allowed on a const iterator?\)) 846 SB
1689 1402 368 ( Proposed Resolution:) 368 SB
1689 1452 982 (  All operations found in the tables can be applied to const) 982 SB
1689 1502 788 (  operands except: ++a a++ --a a-- a= a+= a-=.) 788 SB
1689 1602 497 ( Requestor:      Nathan Myers) 497 SB
