264 2002 794 ( Title:          Distance Type for Output Iterators) 794 SB
264 2052 342 ( Section:        24.1.6) 342 SB
1689 302 324 ( Status:         active) 324 SB
1689 352 219 ( Description:) 219 SB
1689 402 217 (         24.1.6:) 217 SB
1689 452 1038 (    All iterators except output iterator use distance type.  Input) 1038 SB
1689 502 1078 (    iterators have no distance per se but the distance_type is used) 1078 SB
1689 552 1035 (    as a count type for certain algorithms.  A count type would) 1035 SB
1689 602 1033 (    also be useful for certain algorithms using output iterators.) 1033 SB
1689 652 1040 (    The proposal is to define distance_type for output iterators.) 1040 SB
1689 752 1038 (    The recent addition of the iterator_traits proposal defines a) 1038 SB
1689 802 1092 (    separate template iterator for definition of the types associated) 1092 SB
1689 852 1061 (    with an iterator.  Currently category, value, and distance are) 1061 SB
1689 902 1025 (    the types defined.  To have distance not defined for output) 1025 SB
1689 952 1045 (    iterators will require a partial specialization.  It is a cleaner) 1045 SB
1689 1002 1087 (    and more consistent interface to allow distance to be specified) 1087 SB
1689 1052 448 (    for all types of iterators.) 448 SB
1689 1152 645 ( Resolution:  See paper 96-0091/N909) 645 SB
