264 1552 1146 ( Iterator tags could be related by inheritance.  Doing so would allow) 1146 SB
264 1602 1110 ( a more generic solution to algorithms which are multiply defined) 1110 SB
264 1652 1084 ( based on iterator category.  For example, it might be possible to) 1084 SB
264 1702 1156 ( define to versions of an algorithm, one based on output_iterator and) 1156 SB
264 1752 1092 ( one based on forward_iterator.  Iterator categories which inherit) 1092 SB
264 1802 1037 ( from forward_iterator could use the second algorithm.  If the) 1037 SB
264 1852 985 ( categories are inherited, then the based classes should use) 985 SB
264 1902 212 ( inheritance.) 212 SB
264 2002 1011 ( It may also be desirable to provide a mechanism to indicate) 1011 SB
264 2052 1095 ( whether an iterator is constant or mutable.  Different algorithms) 1095 SB
1689 302 1010 ( on iterators could be used if this information was available.) 1010 SB
1689 402 1061 ( Resolution:     Inheritance in iterator tags accepted in N833R1) 1061 SB
1689 452 588 (                 accepted in Santa Cruz.) 588 SB
